The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, June 30, 2003 				 Drinking water used to wash cars
		 Kerb-grabbers: One of  the illegal roadside car-repairing garages that have  sprung up in Bhowanipore. Pictures by Kishor Roy Chowdhury Subhas Ghosh: On Townshend  Road, Beltala Road and Romesh Mitter Road, illegal garages  have sprung up and cars are washed with roadside tap water,  which is also a source of drinking water.																																																													I shall issue a notification against misusing tap water for washing cars. If necessary, billboards and banners will be put up at vital points. A task force will also be formed to create awareness among the people.
